===Reaction to "Life of Brian"===
The death of Brian in the episode "[[Life_of_Brian_(Family_Guy)|Life of Brian]]" was met with massive opposition and anger from ''Family Guy'' fans around the world, many of whom threatened to [[boycott|boycott]] the show, due to Brian's absence. Family Guy's official Facebook and Twitter pages were bombarded with messages and comments from fans, demanding that they bring Brian back. Hostile messages were also directed towards Family Guy's producing staff, including the show's creator, [[Seth_MacFarlane|Seth MacFarlane]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latintimes.com/articles/10569/20131124/brian-griffin-dies-family-guy-twitter-lashes-out-seth-macfarlane.htm#.Up3bLNJdU4k |title=Brian Griffin Dies On 'Family Guy': Twitter Lashes Out at Seth MacFarlane |date=November 25, 2013|author=Maria Valdez|work=[[Latin_Times|Latin Times]]|accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref> The family's new pet, Vinny, subsequently appeared in the opening credits for the next two episodes ("[[Into_Harmony's_Way|Into Harmony's Way]]" and "[[Christmas_Guy|Christmas Guy]]"). Brian's death was averted through time travel in the latter episode, with him returning to the show as a permanent character. MacFarlane later thanked fans "for caring so much about the canine Griffin, he is overcome with gratitude."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comicbook.com/blog/2013/12/15/family-guy-seth-macfarlane-reveals-he-killed-brian-griffin-to-teach-fans-a-lesson/ |title=Family Guy: Seth MacFarlane Reveals He Killed Brian Griffin To Teach Fans A Lesson |date=December 16, 2013|last=|first=|work=ComicBook|accessdate=2013-12-17}}</ref>

Fan petitions sprang up within hours of "Life of Brian"'s first airing, also receiving media attention, including most prominently a [[Change.org|Change.org]] petition directed towards Seth MacFarlane,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/showtracker/la-et-st-family-guy-brian-death-protest-20131125,0,3694745.story#axzz2lhlkPyuS|title='Family Guy' fans protest death of Brian the dog|date=November 25, 2013|author=Patrick Kevin Day|work=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=2012-11-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.yahoo.com/family-guy-fans-protest-death-brian-dog-215224563.html|title='Family Guy' fans protest death of Brian the dog|date=November 25, 2013|work=AFP|publisher=Yahoo! News|accessdate=2013-11-25}}</ref> making the petition one of the fastest-growing entertainment-related petitions on the site,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/11/25/family-guy-petition-to-save-fan-favorite-character|title=Family Guy Petition to Save Fan-Favorite Character|date=November 25, 2013|last=Cornet|first=Roth|publisher=[[IGN|IGN Entertainment]]|accessdate=2013-11-25}}</ref> attracting over 120,000 signatures.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/family-guy-fans-petition-brians-659785?mobile_redirect=false|title='Family Guy' Fans Petition Against Brian's Death|date=November 25, 2013|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|work=[[The_Hollywood_Reporter|The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=2013-11-25}}</ref>

